the bewitch stakes is an american thoroughbred horse race run annually during the second half of april at the keeneland race course in lexington, kentucky. contested on turf over a distance of  1 1⁄2 miles (12 furlongs), it is open to fillies and mares age four and older. currently a grade iii event sponsored by grey goose vodka, it offers a purse of $150,000. inaugurated in 1962, the race is named for calumet farm's great hall of fame filly, bewitch.